<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9931] hll omits value in distributed mode when no values in field</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9931</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given a non-empty bucket, but hll of a field with no values for that bucket domain&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In non-distributed mode, hll returns 0&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In distributed mode, the key+value is omitted entirely&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;We should make these consistent.&lt;br/&gt;
In this case, what makes the most sense is to return 0 for both.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
